# the compiled kernel — `go build -o self .`
/self

# an instance's DERIVED state — rebuilt by `self rehydrate` from the log's
# signed receipts (events.jsonl + .secret are the only source of truth)
**/capabilities/
**/site/

# an instance's SOURCE state — never commit these. .secret is the signing key;
# events.jsonl is a live log. Running `self` with SELF_HOME=. would create them
# right here, and one `git add .` would publish your key. Guard against that.
.secret
events.jsonl
.self/

# python bytecode (mind adapters are scripts)
__pycache__/

# an instance's USER CONTENT — the content-addressed file store. Like
# events.jsonl, it is live instance state, never repo content (root-anchored:
# seeds legitimately carry their own files/ subdirs).
/files/
